==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fragile
<hw>Frag"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fragilis</ets>, from <ets>frangere</ets> to break; cf. F.
<ets>fragile</ets>. See <er>Break</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Frail</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Easily broken; brittle; frail;
delicate; easily destroyed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The state of ivy is tough, and not <qex>fragile</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Brittle; infirm; weak; frail; frangible;
slight.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Frag"ile*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fragility</ent>⟦br⟧
